# Next.js 15 App Router Rules

## Server vs Client Components

Default to Server Components. Add `"use client"` only when the component needs:
- Event listeners (`onClick`, `onChange`, etc.)
- Browser APIs (`window`, `localStorage`, etc.)
- React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, etc.)
- Vercel AI SDK client hooks (`useChat`, `useCompletion`)

**Never place `"use client"` on a page or layout.** Keep pages as Server Components and extract interactive parts into `_components/`.

```typescript
// ✅ app/[locale]/(dashboard)/chat/page.tsx — Server Component
export default async function ChatPage() {
  const supabase = await createClient();
  const { data: history } = await supabase.from("chat_sessions").select("*");
  return <ChatArea history={history} />;
}

// ✅ app/[locale]/(dashboard)/chat/_components/ChatArea.tsx — Client boundary
"use client";

export function ChatArea({ history }: ChatAreaProps) {
  const { messages, input, handleSubmit } = useChat({ api: "/api/chat" });
  // ...
}
```

